{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bruising/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"06351575-ecc2-50ad-a333-42705ee8a940","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d5d810c2-594f-441a-9608-a7f20187eb8a --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field d5d810c2-594f-441a-9608-a7f20187eb8a -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item db7055e5-b046-49fa-b26d-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 07c3bb7f-66c9-4e66-af39-a7f20187eb8a --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 07c3bb7f-66c9-4e66-af39-a7f20187eb8a --><!-- begin field 965235a3-3f6f-44ca-8924-a7f20187eb8a --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 965235a3-3f6f-44ca-8924-a7f20187eb8a --><!-- begin field 18ae8501-43a4-461e-b8da-a7f20187eb8a --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 18ae8501-43a4-461e-b8da-a7f20187eb8a --><!-- begin field f710a942-34e0-451d-a51f-a7f20187eb8a --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field f710a942-34e0-451d-a51f-a7f20187eb8a --><!-- begin field 051def86-5d24-4603-9b1a-a7f20187eb8a --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 051def86-5d24-4603-9b1a-a7f20187eb8a --><!-- begin field 163b2c44-6cd7-4f27-82d6-a7f20187eb8a --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 163b2c44-6cd7-4f27-82d6-a7f20187eb8a --><!-- end item db7055e5-b046-49fa-b26d-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"0695329d-6789-5f2e-bdd4-23fa7e538a68","topicId":"a2ffbaff-593f-430e-ba07-22a88a81554f","topicName":"Bruising","slug":"bruising","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2016","chapters":[{"id":"cd3da1a8-ef20-5a0a-b9ee-42193acd5123","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"23fb83e3-3c5a-52f9-abe6-74a66bb0fbdd","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"07d092b9-1fc7-5bde-b6fd-0844b88c2e2d","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"690311f9-d70d-5981-a8c1-217bbb32f72b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"6c40fbc1-a0ca-53e5-ac89-9092d1659ad3","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"97948439-efdb-5ee7-a48d-1a8021361f1c","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"63d16865-3aee-5e25-84e7-fadaaa1cb8d2","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5139834d-a623-5be5-9d54-877a38c4327e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"48d78c1e-438d-56eb-9e93-9293df84a7cf","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"158558